    "content": "# API Reference\n\nThe Badget API provides programmatic access to all link management features. This REST API uses JSON for request and response data.\n\n## Base URL\n\nAll API requests should be made to:\n\n```\nhttps://api.badget.app\n```\n\n## Authentication\n\nAuthenticate your API requests using a Bearer token in the Authorization header:\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  https://api.badget.app/links\n```\n\n### Getting Your API Key\n\n1. Log in to your Badget dashboard\n2. Navigate to Settings â†’ API Keys\n3. Click \"Generate New Key\"\n4. Copy and securely store your key\n\n## Rate Limiting\n\nAPI requests are limited to:\n\n- **Free Plan**: 1,000 requests per hour\n- **Pro Plan**: 10,000 requests per hour\n- **Enterprise**: Custom limits\n\nRate limit headers are included in all responses:\n\n```\nX-RateLimit-Limit: 1000\nX-RateLimit-Remaining: 999\nX-RateLimit-Reset: 1640995200\n```\n\n## Links\n\n### Create a Link\n\nCreate a new shortened link.\n\n```http\nPOST /links\n```\n\n**Parameters:**\n\n| Name | Type | Required | Description |\n|------|------|----------|-------------|\n| `url` | string | Yes | The destination URL |\n| `alias` | string | No | Custom alias for the short link |\n| `title` | string | No | Link title for tracking |\n| `tags` | array | No | Array of tag strings |\n| `expiresAt` | string | No | ISO date when link expires |\n\n**Example Request:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://api.badget.app/links \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"url\": \"https://example.com\",\n    \"alias\": \"my-link\",\n    \"title\": \"Example Website\",\n    \"tags\": [\"example\", \"test\"]\n  }'\n```\n\n**Example Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"clr123abc\",\n  \"shortUrl\": \"https://bdg.et/my-link\",\n  \"url\": \"https://example.com\",\n  \"alias\": \"my-link\",\n  \"title\": \"Example Website\",\n  \"tags\": [\"example\", \"test\"],\n  \"clicks\": 0,\n  \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"expiresAt\": null\n}\n```\n\n### Get Link Details\n\nRetrieve details for a specific link.\n\n```http\nGET /links/{id}\n```\n\n**Example Request:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  https://api.badget.app/links/clr123abc\n```\n\n### Update a Link\n\nUpdate an existing link's properties.\n\n```http\nPUT /links/{id}\n```\n\n**Example Request:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -X PUT https://api.badget.app/links/clr123abc \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"title\": \"Updated Title\",\n    \"tags\": [\"updated\", \"example\"]\n  }'\n```\n\n### Delete a Link\n\nDelete a link permanently.\n\n```http\nDELETE /links/{id}\n```\n\n**Example Request:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -X DELETE https://api.badget.app/links/clr123abc \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\"\n```\n\n### List Links\n\nGet a paginated list of your links.\n\n```http\nGET /links\n```\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n\n| Name | Type | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `limit` | number | Number of links to return (max 100) |\n| `offset` | number | Number of links to skip |\n| `tag` | string | Filter by tag |\n| `search` | string | Search in title and URL |\n\n**Example Request:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  \"https://api.badget.app/links?limit=10&tag=example\"\n```\n\n## Analytics\n\n### Get Link Analytics\n\nRetrieve analytics data for a specific link.\n\n```http\nGET /analytics/links/{id}\n```\n\n**Query Parameters:**\n\n| Name | Type | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| `period` | string | Time period: `1h`, `24h`, `7d`, `30d`, `90d` |\n| `interval` | string | Data interval: `hour`, `day`, `week` |\n| `country` | string | Filter by country code |\n| `referrer` | string | Filter by referrer domain |\n\n**Example Request:**\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  \"https://api.badget.app/analytics/links/clr123abc?period=7d&interval=day\"\n```\n\n**Example Response:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"id\": \"clr123abc\",\n  \"totalClicks\": 1250,\n  \"uniqueClicks\": 890,\n  \"clicksByDate\": [\n    {\n      \"date\": \"2024-01-15\",\n      \"clicks\": 180,\n      \"uniqueClicks\": 150\n    }\n  ],\n  \"topCountries\": [\n    {\n      \"country\": \"US\",\n      \"clicks\": 450\n    },\n    {\n      \"country\": \"GB\",\n      \"clicks\": 200\n    }\n  ],\n  \"topReferrers\": [\n    {\n      \"referrer\": \"twitter.com\",\n      \"clicks\": 300\n    },\n    {\n      \"referrer\": \"linkedin.com\",\n      \"clicks\": 150\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Webhooks\n\nSet up webhooks to receive real-time notifications about link events.\n\n### Webhook Events\n\n- `link.clicked` - When a link is clicked\n- `link.created` - When a new link is created\n- `link.updated` - When a link is updated\n- `link.deleted` - When a link is deleted\n\n### Example Webhook Payload\n\n```json\n{\n  \"event\": \"link.clicked\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"linkId\": \"clr123abc\",\n    \"shortUrl\": \"https://bdg.et/my-link\",\n    \"clickedAt\": \"2024-01-15T14:30:00Z\",\n    \"country\": \"US\",\n    \"referrer\": \"twitter.com\",\n    \"userAgent\": \"Mozilla/5.0...\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\nThe API uses conventional HTTP response codes:\n\n- `200` - Success\n- `400` - Bad Request\n- `401` - Unauthorized\n- `403` - Forbidden\n- `404` - Not Found\n- `429` - Rate Limited\n- `500` - Internal Server Error\n\n**Error Response Format:**\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"INVALID_URL\",\n    \"message\": \"The provided URL is not valid\",\n    \"details\": \"URL must include http:// or https://\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## SDK and Libraries\n\nOfficial libraries are available for popular programming languages:\n\n- **JavaScript/Node.js**: `npm install @badget/js`\n- **Python**: `pip install badget`\n- **PHP**: `composer require badget/php`\n- **Go**: `go get github.com/badget/go`\n\n### JavaScript Example\n\n```javascript\nimport { Badget } from '@badget/js';\n\nconst badget = new Badget('YOUR_API_KEY');\n\n// Create a link\nconst link = await badget.links.create({\n  url: 'https://example.com',\n  alias: 'my-link'\n});\n\nconsole.log(link.shortUrl); // https://bdg.et/my-link\n```\n\n## Support\n\nNeed help with the API? Here are your options:\n\n- **Documentation**: Check our comprehensive guides\n- **Community**: Join our Discord community\n- **Support**: Email support@badget.app\n- **Status**: Check status.badget.app for API status\n\nFor feature requests or bug reports, please use our GitHub repository.",
