    "title": "Troubleshooting Common Issues",
    "description": "Solutions to common problems and frequently asked questions about using Badget.",
    "publishedAt": "2024-01-25",
    "updatedAt": "2024-01-28",
    "summary": "Quick solutions and troubleshooting steps for the most common Badget issues.",
    "tags": [
      "troubleshooting",
      "faq",
      "support",
      "issues"
    ],
    "content": "# Troubleshooting Common Issues\n\nThis guide covers solutions to the most frequently encountered issues with Badget.\n\n## Link Creation Issues\n\n### \"Invalid URL\" Error\n\n**Problem**: Getting an error when trying to create a short link.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Ensure your URL includes `http://` or `https://`\n2. Check for typos in the URL\n3. Verify the destination website is accessible\n4. Remove any special characters that might cause issues\n\n**Example**:\n```\nâŒ Wrong: example.com\nâœ… Correct: https://example.com\n```\n\n### Alias Already Taken\n\n**Problem**: Custom alias you want is already in use.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Try a different alias variation\n2. Add numbers or descriptive words\n3. Use your brand name as a prefix\n4. Check if you already created this alias previously\n\n### Link Not Redirecting\n\n**Problem**: Short link isn't redirecting to the intended destination.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Check if the original URL is still valid\n2. Verify the link hasn't expired\n3. Clear your browser cache\n4. Try opening in an incognito/private window\n5. Check if the link has been disabled\n\n## Analytics and Tracking\n\n### Missing Click Data\n\n**Problem**: Analytics showing zero clicks despite traffic.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Verify tracking is enabled for the link\n2. Check if you're testing with the same IP repeatedly\n3. Ensure JavaScript is enabled in browsers\n4. Look for bot traffic filtering settings\n5. Check the time range in your analytics view\n\n### Incorrect Geographic Data\n\n**Problem**: Location data seems inaccurate.\n\n**Explanation**: Geographic data is based on IP addresses, which can be:\n- VPN or proxy servers\n- Corporate networks\n- Mobile carrier locations\n- CDN endpoints\n\n**Note**: This is a limitation of IP-based geolocation, not a bug.\n\n### Analytics Delays\n\n**Problem**: Click data not appearing immediately.\n\n**Normal Behavior**: Analytics may take 5-15 minutes to update due to:\n- Data processing pipelines\n- Cache invalidation\n- Real-time vs. batch processing\n\n## Custom Domain Issues\n\n### Domain Not Verifying\n\n**Problem**: Custom domain verification failing.\n\n**Troubleshooting Steps**:\n1. **Check DNS Records**:\n   ```bash\n   # Check CNAME record\n   dig your-domain.com CNAME\n   \n   # Check A record\n   dig your-domain.com A\n   ```\n\n2. **Common DNS Issues**:\n   - TTL too high (should be 3600 or lower)\n   - Incorrect record values\n   - DNS propagation delays (up to 24 hours)\n   - Cloudflare proxy enabled (should be DNS only)\n\n3. **Verify Configuration**:\n   - Subdomain: `CNAME short -> cname.badget.app`\n   - Root domain: `A @ -> 76.76.19.123`\n\n### SSL Certificate Problems\n\n**Problem**: SSL certificate not provisioning.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Wait 15-30 minutes after domain verification\n2. Ensure domain is publicly accessible\n3. Check for conflicting SSL certificates\n4. Contact support if issues persist beyond 1 hour\n\n## API Integration Issues\n\n### Authentication Errors\n\n**Problem**: Getting 401 Unauthorized responses.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. **Check API Key Format**:\n   ```bash\n   # Correct format\n   Authorization: Bearer bdg_1234567890abcdef\n   ```\n\n2. **Common Mistakes**:\n   - Missing \"Bearer \" prefix\n   - Extra spaces in the header\n   - Using test key in production\n   - Expired or revoked key\n\n3. **Generate New Key**:\n   - Go to Settings â†’ API Keys\n   - Click \"Generate New Key\"\n   - Update your applications\n\n### Rate Limiting\n\n**Problem**: Getting 429 Too Many Requests errors.\n\n**Understanding Rate Limits**:\n- Free: 1,000 requests/hour\n- Pro: 10,000 requests/hour\n- Enterprise: Custom limits\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Implement exponential backoff\n2. Cache responses when possible\n3. Upgrade to higher plan\n4. Contact support for higher limits\n\n### API Response Errors\n\n**Problem**: Unexpected API responses or errors.\n\n**Debugging Steps**:\n1. **Check Request Format**:\n   ```bash\n   curl -X POST https://api.badget.app/links \\\n     -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_KEY\" \\\n     -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n     -d '{\"url\": \"https://example.com\"}'\n   ```\n\n2. **Validate JSON Syntax**\n3. **Check Required Fields**\n4. **Review API Documentation**\n\n## Account and Billing\n\n### Login Issues\n\n**Problem**: Can't access your account.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. **Password Reset**: Use \"Forgot Password\" link\n2. **Check Email**: Look in spam/junk folders\n3. **Browser Issues**: Clear cache and cookies\n4. **Two-Factor Authentication**: Ensure access to your authenticator app\n\n### Billing Questions\n\n**Problem**: Issues with subscription or payments.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Check payment method expiration\n2. Verify billing address information\n3. Contact your bank for declined payments\n4. Review billing email for notifications\n5. Contact support for billing disputes\n\n## Performance Issues\n\n### Slow Link Creation\n\n**Problem**: Links taking too long to create.\n\n**Potential Causes**:\n- High server load\n- Large destination page validation\n- Network connectivity issues\n- Browser performance problems\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Try creating simpler links first\n2. Use a different browser\n3. Check your internet connection\n4. Contact support if persistent\n\n### Dashboard Loading Slowly\n\n**Problem**: Analytics dashboard loading slowly.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Reduce the date range\n2. Clear browser cache\n3. Disable browser extensions\n4. Try incognito mode\n5. Check for large datasets\n\n## Mobile App Issues\n\n### App Crashes\n\n**Problem**: Mobile app crashing frequently.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Update to latest app version\n2. Restart your device\n3. Clear app cache/data\n4. Reinstall the app\n5. Check device storage space\n\n### Sync Issues\n\n**Problem**: Data not syncing between devices.\n\n**Solutions**:\n1. Ensure internet connectivity\n2. Log out and log back in\n3. Force app refresh\n4. Check account permissions\n5. Update app to latest version\n\n## Getting Additional Help\n\n### Before Contacting Support\n\n1. **Search Documentation**: Check this help center\n2. **Check Status Page**: Visit status.badget.app\n3. **Try Different Browser**: Rule out browser issues\n4. **Gather Information**:\n   - Error messages (exact text)\n   - Steps to reproduce\n   - Browser/device information\n   - Screenshots if applicable\n\n### Contact Options\n\n1. **Live Chat**: Available 9 AM - 6 PM PST\n2. **Email Support**: support@badget.app\n3. **Community Forum**: community.badget.app\n4. **Priority Support**: Enterprise customers only\n\n### What to Include\n\nWhen contacting support, please include:\n- Account email address\n- Detailed description of the issue\n- Steps you've already tried\n- Error messages or screenshots\n- Browser and device information\n\n## Frequently Asked Questions\n\n### Can I edit a link after creation?\n\nYes, you can update:\n- Destination URL\n- Title and description\n- Tags and metadata\n- Expiration date\n\nYou cannot change the short URL alias after creation.\n\n### How long do links last?\n\n- **Free accounts**: Links last indefinitely unless deleted\n- **Paid accounts**: Same, plus option to set expiration dates\n- **Expired links**: Return 404 error page\n\n### Can I see who clicked my links?\n\nFor privacy reasons, Badget doesn't show individual user information. You can see:\n- Aggregate statistics\n- Geographic regions\n- Device types\n- Referrer sources\n\n### Is there a mobile app?\n\nYes! Badget has mobile apps for:\n- iOS (App Store)\n- Android (Google Play)\n- Features: Link creation, analytics, QR codes\n\nStill having issues? [Contact our support team](/contact) - we're here to help!",
